%X Full-text retrieval systems often use either a bitmap or an inverted file to
identify which documents contain which terms, so that the documents containing
any combination of query terms can be quickly located.  Bitmaps of term
occurrences are large, but are usually sparse, and thus are amenable to a
variety of compression techniques.  Here we consider techniques in which the
encoding of each bitvector within the bitmap is parameterised, so that a
different code can be used for each bitvector.  Our experimental results show
that the new methods yield better compression than previous techniques.

