%X The dominant approaches to information retrieval system design are based on
rational theory and cognitive engineering.  However, these theories as well as
approaches in other disciplines, reviewed in this paper, do not account for
communication, or interaction, among design participants which is critical to
design outcomes.  This research attempts to develop a descriptive design model
that accounts for communication among users, designers, and developers
